                  </hi>. The prisoner ought not to have made these hay-covers at his own house—I gave him the money to pay Wurr for making them—here is an entry in my diary: "27th May, 1851: one wagon-cover made, and two cart-covers"—it is his duty to deliver them to Wurr—Wurr is not here—it was two tarpaulings I gave him on 6th June—the covers are mixed up together.</p>
